<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Web" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Web,</orth> 1) any thing woven, texture: <bibl n="shak. ven 991" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 991</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lc 95" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 95</bibl> (a downy beard called so). <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.83" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.243" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 243</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.69" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 69</bibl>.<lb />2) <emph>the pin and w.,</emph> a disorder of the eye, consisting in a dusky film hindering the sight: <cit><quote>all eyes blind with the pin and w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.291" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 291</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he gives the w. and the pin, squints the eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 122</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>